()🔷 ProvisioningPolicy kya hai?
👉 ProvisioningPolicy =
Rules / Template / Form jo decide karta hai ki
➡️ Account create/update/delete karte time kaun-kaun se fields chahiye
➡️ Kaise values fill hongi
➡️ Mandatory kya hai
📌 Simple line me:-
👉 “Account banate waqt kya data dena hai aur kaise dena hai” — ye ProvisioningPolicy decide karta hai.

🔷 Real Life Example:-
Maan le tu user ko Active Directory me create kar raha hai:
To system bolega:-
username chahiye
password chahiye
email chahiye
OU (Organizational Unit) chahiye
👉 Ye sab kisne define kiya?
➡️ ProvisioningPolicy
-----------------------------------------------------
🔷 Ye kya karta hai:-
1️⃣ Form define karta hai
Account create karte time ka UI form
Kaun fields dikhenge

2️⃣ Mandatory fields decide karta hai:-
Example:-
username → required
password → required
phone → optional

3️⃣ Default values set karta hai:-
Example:-
country = "India"
status = "Active"

4️⃣ Value generation logic:-
Example:-
username = firstname + lastname
email = firstname.lastname@company.com

5️⃣ Validation karta hai:-
Example:-
password length >= 8
email valid format

6️⃣ Identity se mapping karta hai:-
Example:-
Identity.firstname → account.givenName
Identity.email → account.mail
----------------------------------------------------------
🔷 ProvisioningPolicy ke andar kya hota hai?
Internally ye object hota hai:-

🔹 1. Fields (sabse important):-
Har field ek object hota hai:-
name → "username"
type → string
required → true/false
defaultValue → "test"
source → identity attribute

🔹 2. Field Attributes:-
Har field ke andar:-
displayName
description
required flag
multiValued ya nahi
readOnly ya editable

🔹 3. Field Mapping:-
Identity → Target system mapping

🔹 4. Rules/Scripts:-
Custom logic:-
username generate karna
password generate karna

🔹 5. Operation Type
--------------------------------------------------------
🔷 Flow me kaise use hota hai?
Jab tu ye karta hai:-
ProvisioningPlan plan = new ProvisioningPlan();
👉 System internally karta hai:-
Application check karta hai
ProvisioningPolicy uthata hai
Required fields validate karta hai
Missing values fill karta hai
AccountRequest banata hai

🔷 DB me store hota hai kya?
👉 ✅ Haan bhai, store hota hai
📍 Table:-
spt_provisioning_policy
DB me kya store hota hai?
policy name
application reference
XML format me fields
rules / mappings
------------------------------------------------------------
🔷 Developer likh ye sakta hai?
👉 ❌ Direct code me nahi likhta usually
👉 ✅ UI ya XML config se define hota hai
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔷 1️⃣ Operation Type kya hota hai?
👉 Operation Type =
Ye batata hai ki account pe kaunsa action perform ho raha hai,

🔥 Main Operation Types:-
✅ 1. CREATE:-
👉 Naya account banana
Use case:-
New employee join hua
Account AD / DB / App me create hoga
Example:-
accountRequest.setOperation(AccountRequest.Operation.Create);

✅ 2. MODIFY:-
👉 Existing account update karna
Use case:-
Role change
Email update
Department change
accountRequest.setOperation(AccountRequest.Operation.Modify);

✅ 3. DELETE:-
👉 Account remove karna
Use case:-
Employee resign
Account delete
accountRequest.setOperation(AccountRequest.Operation.Delete);

✅ 4. DISABLE:-
👉 Account disable (soft delete)
Use case:-
Temporary block
Leave pe hai user
accountRequest.setOperation(AccountRequest.Operation.Disable);

✅ 5. ENABLE:-
👉 Disabled account ko wapas active karna
accountRequest.setOperation(AccountRequest.Operation.Enable);

✅ 6. LOCK / UNLOCK:-
👉 Account lock ya unlock
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔷 2️⃣ Types of ProvisioningPolicy:-
👉 Ye Operation Type ke basis pe hi divide hoti hai 🔥

🔥 1. Create ProvisioningPolicy:-
👉 Jab Operation = CREATE

Ye kya karta hai?
Required fields check karta hai
Default values fill karta hai
Username/password generate karta hai
📌 Example fields:-
username (required)
password (required)
email

🔥 2. Modify ProvisioningPolicy:-
👉 Jab Operation = MODIFY

Ye kya karta hai?
Sirf update hone wale fields handle karta hai
Sab fields required nahi hote
📌 Example:-
phone update
department change

🔥 3. Delete ProvisioningPolicy:-
👉 Jab Operation = DELETE
Ye kya karta hai?
Usually minimal data chahiye
Sirf identify karta hai account ko

📌 Example:-
nativeIdentity (username)

🔥 4. Disable / Enable Policy:-
👉 Jab Operation = DISABLE / ENABLE
Ye kya karta hai?
Account status change karta hai
Mostly extra fields nahi chahiye

🔥 5. Role-Based ProvisioningPolicy:-
👉 Jab koi Role assign hota hai
Ye kya karta hai?
Automatically account create/update karta hai
Role ke basis pe fields fill hoti hain

📌 Example:-
Role = "Manager" ko assign kiya toh 
→ system automatically:-
access dega
attributes set karega
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 1️⃣ Basic Methods:-
✅ getName():-
👉 Policy ka naam deta hai
String name = policy.getName();

✅ getApplication():-
👉 Ye batata hai kis application ke liye policy hai,
Application app = policy.getApplication();

✅ getType():-
👉 Policy ka type (Create / Modify)
String type = policy.getType();

✅ setType(String type):-
policy.setType("Create");
---------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 2️⃣ Field Handling Methods:-
Field Handling Methods – Kyu use hote hain?
👉 Simple line:-
ProvisioningPolicy ke fields ko read / check / modify karne ke liye.

✅ 1. Required fields check karne ke liye:-
👉 Example:-
username required hai ya nahi
password missing hai ya nahi

✅ 2. Dynamic logic likhne ke liye:-
👉 Example:-
agar username nahi diya → generate karo
agar email nahi hai → default do

✅ 3. Debugging ke liye:-
👉 Logs me dekhte hain:-
kaun-kaun fields aa rahe hain
required kya hai

✅ 4. Mapping samajhne ke liye:-
👉 Identity → Account mapping kaise ho rahi hai

🔥 Important Field Handling Methods:-
✅ getFields():-
👉 Sare fields deta hai

✅ getField("name"):-
👉 Specific field deta hai

✅ addField():-
👉 Runtime me field add kar sakte ho (rare case)

✅ removeField():-
👉 Field hata sakte ho

🔷 💻 Code + Output Example:-
ProvisioningPolicy policy = application.getProvisioningPolicy();

for (ProvisioningPolicy.Field field : policy.getFields()) {

    System.out.println("Field Name: " + field.getName());
    System.out.println("Required: " + field.isRequired());
    System.out.println("Type: " + field.getType());
    System.out.println("Default Value: " + field.getValue());
    System.out.println("------");
}
🖥️ Output (Example):-
Field Name: username
Required: true
Type: string
Default Value: null
------

Field Name: password
Required: true
Type: string
Default Value: null
------

Field Name: email
Required: false
Type: string
Default Value: test@gmail.com
------
---------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 3️⃣ Field Class ke Methods (Nested Class):-
👉 ProvisioningPolicy.Field sabse important hai 🔥

✅ getName():-
field.getName();

✅ getDisplayName():-
field.getDisplayName();

✅ isRequired():-
👉 Mandatory hai ya nahi
field.isRequired();

✅ setRequired(boolean):-
field.setRequired(true);

✅ getType():-
👉 Data type (string, boolean, etc.)
field.getType();

✅ getValue():-
👉 Default value ya assigned value
Object value = field.getValue();

✅ setValue(Object value)
field.setValue("testUser");

✅ getSource():-
👉 Value kahan se aayegi (Identity attribute etc.)
field.getSource();

✅ setSource(String source):-
field.setSource("identity.firstname");

✅ isMultiValued():-
field.isMultiValued();

✅ isReadOnly():-
field.isReadOnly();

🔥 4️⃣ Advanced Methods (Real Use Cases)
✅ apply():-
👉 Policy ko apply karta hai plan pe (internally use hota hai)
policy.apply(plan);
📌 Note: Mostly internal use, directly rarely call karte hain

✅ validate():-
👉 Fields validate karta hai
policy.validate();

✅ toXml():-
👉 Policy ko XML me convert karta hai
String xml = policy.toXml();

✅ fromXml():-
👉 XML se policy banata hai
ProvisioningPolicy policy = ProvisioningPolicy.fromXml(xml);

🔥 5️⃣ Utility Methods:-
✅ getDescription():-
policy.getDescription();

✅ setDescription():-
policy.setDescription("Create Account Policy");

✅ isEmpty():-
👉 Check karta hai koi field hai ya nahi
policy.isEmpty();
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔷 🔥 validate() kya karta hai?
👉 validate() = Policy ke rules ke against data check karta hai
📌 Simple:-
👉 “Jo data diya hai wo sahi hai ya nahi”
🔥 validate() kya kya check karta hai?

✅ 1. Required fields present hai ya nahi
👉 agar missing:
❌ Error throw karega

✅ 2. Data type check
👉 Example:
string me number na aa jaye
boolean valid ho

✅ 3. Value constraints
👉 Example:
password length
allowed values

✅ 4. Mapping correctness
👉 source valid hai ya nahi
(identity attribute exist karta hai ya nahi)

✅ 5. Multi-valued fields check
👉 agar list expected hai to list hi aaye

✅ 6. Read-only fields modify na ho
👉 agar readOnly hai → change nahi hone dega.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
